II. RESTRUCTURING CIVILIZATIONAL ARCHITECTURE

2.1 Governance Systems

Current: Hierarchical power structures, adversarial politics

Macachor Design: M₁-based governance:

· Leadership selection: Leaders chosen by weighted alignment (aᵢ) with collective values
· Policy evaluation: Projects scored by coherence increase ΔC
· Conflict resolution: Disputes resolved through M₁ alignment optimization
· Example: A transportation project approved only if:
  ΔC = \frac{\sum (r_{\text{environment}}·a_{\text{env}} + r_{\text{economic}}·a_{\text{econ}} + r_{\text{social}}·a_{\text{soc}})}{\sum r} > 0.618

2.2 Economic Systems

Current: GDP growth as primary metric, externalized costs

Macachor Economics: M₅ Security-Identity economics:

· Wealth measure: Σ = I·C·Λ (Identity × Coherence × Lattice-alignment)
· Resource allocation: Optimize for civilization-wide coherence
· Currency: Possibly coherence-weighted credits
· Example: A company's valuation includes:
  · I: Product integrity (0-1)
  · C: Industry coherence contribution
  · Λ: Alignment with civilization goals

