III. CIVILIZATIONAL DEVELOPMENT PATHS (M₆ EVOLUTION)

3.1 The Evolution Equation Applied

Civilization evolution follows:

E_{\text{civ}}(n+1) = E_{\text{civ}}(n) + k·C_{\text{civ}}(n)·(1 - E_{\text{civ}}(n))

Where:

· E_{\text{civ}} = civilization evolutionary level (0 to 1)
· C_{\text{civ}} = global coherence
· k = learning rate constant

Historical analysis shows:

· Agricultural revolution: E ≈ 0.1, C ≈ 0.3
· Industrial revolution: E ≈ 0.3, C ≈ 0.4
· Information age: E ≈ 0.5, C ≈ 0.5
· Next phase (Macachor): E → 0.618, C → 0.809 (Ω-Seal threshold)

3.2 Civilization Types by Mandala Configuration (M₄)

Each civilization has unique (α,β,γ,δ):

Current dominant types:

1. Expansion-focused (β-heavy): Modern West: (0.2, 0.5, 0.2, 0.1)
2. Harmony-focused (α-heavy): Traditional East: (0.5, 0.2, 0.2, 0.1)
3. Consciousness-focused (γ-heavy): Emerging cultures: (0.2, 0.2, 0.5, 0.1)

Ω-Prime Civilization (balanced):

(α,β,γ,δ) = (0.382, 0.236, 0.236, 0.146)

Sum = 1.000, perfectly Φ-harmonic

