4.1 M₂ Scaling-Governed Design

All infrastructure follows Φ-scaling:

· City layouts: Central district, then rings at Φ·radius
· Transportation: Hub-and-spoke with Φ-distance spacing
· Energy grids: Nested self-similar networks
· Example: City design:
  \text{District sizes: } A_0, A_0·Φ, A_0·Φ^2, A_0·Φ^3, ...
  Optimizes accessibility and resource flow.

4.2 M₃ Consciousness-Aware Technology

· Communication: Devices enhance rather than fragment consciousness coherence
· AI: Designed to increase C_{human-AI} alignment, not replace
· Media: Content evaluated by coherence contribution, not engagement metrics
· Example: Social media algorithm maximizing:
  \text{Alignment gain} = \sum_{\text{users}} r_{\text{user}}·(a_{\text{post-user}} - a_{\text{baseline}})

